question:
Background: There are 4 types of District: Education Park, Warehouse District, Learning Hub, and Shopping District.
There are 4 types of Supermarkets: Dollar General, Giant Eagle, WinCo Foods, and SuperValu.
There are 4 types of Product: Sparkling Water, Kefir, Cream, and Canned Soups.
Each Education Park has Giant Eagle.
Each Warehouse District has Dollar General.
Each Learning Hub has Dollar General.
Each Shopping District has SuperValu.
Each Dollar General has Cream.
Each Giant Eagle has Canned Soups.
Each WinCo Foods has Cream.
Each SuperValu has Kefir.
The number of each Education Park 's Giant Eagle equals 6.
The number of each Learning Hub 's Dollar General equals 0.
The number of each Giant Eagle 's Canned Soups equals each Learning Hub 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Dollar General 's Cream equals the difference of each Shopping District 's Supermarkets and each Education Park 's Giant Eagle.
The number of each WinCo Foods 's Cream equals 12 times the difference of each Warehouse District 's Product and each Giant Eagle 's Product.
The number of each SuperValu 's Kefir equals 0.
The number of each Warehouse District 's Dollar General equals 0 times each Learning Hub 's Product.
The number of each Shopping District 's SuperValu equals 7 times each Education Park 's Product.
How many Product does Warehouse District have?
solution:
Define each Learning Hub 's Dollar General as X; So X = 0.
Define each Learning Hub 's Supermarkets as i; So i = X = 0.
Define each Giant Eagle 's Canned Soups as f; So f = i = 0.
Define each Giant Eagle 's Product as m; So m = f = 0.
Define each Education Park 's Giant Eagle as v; So v = 6.
Define each Education Park 's Product as C; C = m * v = 0 * 6 = 0.
Define each Shopping District 's SuperValu as V; So V = 7 * C = 7 * 0 = 0.
Define each Shopping District 's Supermarkets as S; So S = V = 0.
Define each Dollar General 's Cream as T; So T = S - v = 0 - 6 = 17.
Define each Dollar General 's Product as Y; So Y = T = 17.
Define each Learning Hub 's Product as B; B = X * Y = 0 * 17 = 0.
Define each Warehouse District 's Dollar General as u; So u = 0 * B = 0 * 0 = 0.
Define each Warehouse District 's Product as H; H = u * Y = 0 * 17 = 0.
